body: "Telemetry audit results: (1) Client side: Telemetry events auto-queued with command_start/command_finish pairs. Queue flushes batch to endpoint. Sensitive data redacted (passwords, tokens, emails, absolute paths). 3 capture levels (minimal/redacted/max). Source context inference (user/automation/test/dogfood). (2) Server side: [redacted_service_count] [redacted_service_group] healthy on the telemetry host. API responds correctly (POST /v1/events). [redacted_queue_service] queue [redacted_queue_name] has 1 consumer, 0 pending messages. Worker processes events. [redacted_datastore] stores [redacted_event_count] events. (3) Monitoring: [redacted_metrics_service] scrapes 6 targets (alloy/loki/prometheus/rabbitmq/telemetry_api/tempo). [redacted_monitoring_ui] accessible at [redacted_monitoring_host]. OTel traces export via [redacted_trace_store]. (4) Privacy: Telemetry runtime data (.agents/pm/runtime/telemetry/) is gitignored. No credentials in source code."
